modules.description: Handles low-level byte manipulation and buffer management for efficient serialization. Operates on byte arrays, buffers, and custom data structures to enable precise control over memory usage during serialization. Used to implement protocol-specific serializers, such as a JSON encoder that leverages vectorized writes for high-performance network transmission.

Handles asynchronous serialization of Faraday buffers, enabling streaming data through a yield function. Operates on Faraday.t and bigstring iovec structures for efficient I/O operations. Used to write buffer segments to file descriptors in non-blocking network or file operations.
